                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47265",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bytehoven",
                        "name": "bytehoven",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Ke\u00dfler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is also an infinite loop when giving values higher than 1.0E+308(php float range)\r\nto the constructor. Maybe there should be some range checks?\r\n\r\nHere\u00b4s the code leads to infinite loop, because of the float inv (e.g. with 1.0E+309)\r\nZend_Date_DateObject protected function date()\r\nwhile (abs($tempstamp) > 0x7FFFFFFF) {\r\n$tempstamp -= (86400 * 23376);\r\n}\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
